  "function_path": "sklearn/decomposition/_fastica.py",
  "function_name": "_fit_transform",
  "justification": "The _fit_transform method of the FastICA class is the core fitting procedure for ICA. It performs all the steps described: (1) validates and transposes input data X of shape (n_samples, n_features), (2) selects the nonlinearity function (logcosh, exp, cube, or callable) via lines 582-591, (3) determines n_components by clamping to min(n_samples, n_features) on lines 599-605, (4) performs optional whitening by centering data (line 609-610) and computing whitening matrix via eigendecomposition (eigh) or SVD (lines 613-629), (5) initializes unmixing weight matrix w_init randomly if not provided (lines 645-649), (6) delegates to either _ica_par (parallel/symmetric decorrelation) or _ica_def (deflation algorithm) for fixed-point iteration (lines 667-670), (7) computes separated sources S of shape (n_samples, n_components) if compute_sources=True (lines 675-689), else returns None (line 681), and (8) sets instance attributes: components_, mixing_, mean_, whitening_, _unmixing, and n_iter_ (lines 691-698, 673). This matches the required behavior exactly."
}

